[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    165[0m:[38;5;10m[49m ### Networking Expert Review
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    166[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    167[0m:[38;5;10m[49m #### What's Done Well
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    168[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    169[0m:[38;5;10m[49m - VPC enforcement framed correctly: "Production: SageMaker training and inference in VPC with VPC endpoints for S3, Kinesis, CloudWatch Logs, and KMS. Required for HIPAA workloads."
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    170[0m:[38;5;10m[49m - The Kinesis-vs-HealthLake decision is correctly framed at the network-architecture level: HealthLake is a managed FHIR-aware store with its own ingestion endpoint; Kinesis is a generic stream that the pipeline reads via VPC endpoint.
